item.title: CVE-2024-28125|2024-10-10T01:46:32.023Z -- unclebob -- fitnesse
item.description: FitNesse all releases allows a remote authenticated attacker to execute arbitrary OS commands. Note: A contributor of FitNesse has claimed that this is not a vulnerability but a product specification and this is currently under further investigation.
